# Abyss
> The roguelike endgame run got a major content and balance pass.
Added autocast cards: Chain Lightning, Frost Nova, Meteor Rain, and Sanctuary
Added amplifier cards Stormlord and Thornmail that boost your equipped kit
Added combat cards: Frostbite, Soul Harvest, Detonate, and Avarice
Added spell-cast cards: Resonance, Arcane Overflow, and Echo
Added summoner card Void Spawn and adjacent-pulse card Orbiting Blades
Added death-prevention cards Aegis Protocol and the legendary Phoenix
Added cards Predator, Glass Cannon, and Lifeweave
Added enemy Key Modifiers: Cursed Ground, Vampiric, Adrenaline, and Reanimator
Added encounter types: Horde, Swarm, and Elite Pack
Added the Void Walker enemy roster (Bruiser / Seer / Swarmling)
Added a deck framework with slot caps, rarity caps, and Dissolve (respec)
Added the Upgrade Tome and permanent Upgrade Picker meta-progression
Added a "My Upgrades" tab and per-type HUD breakdown to the portal
Added procedural boss rounds
Added risk-vs-reward coin rewards that also scale XP
Rebalanced enemy roster sizes for fairer fights
Rebalanced the Upgrade Tome to a single escalating cost with free rerolls
Capped damage reduction at 45%
Fixed Void Spawn dealing no damage and stalling encounters
Fixed several crashes (summon autocast, spell backfire, on-kill spawns)
Fixed reward text being cut off in the portal
Disabled the combat speed penalty for bosses

# Card Collection
Rebalanced all cards to scale with slot investment
Fixed a damage-reduction bug that doubled on relog
Fixed card stat values being truncated or shown incorrectly
Card descriptions now display their real live values instead of placeholder text

# General
Added character appearance and Might to the character list
